One random symptom is anxiety and depression.‚Å† Even in low levels, mold can trigger anxiety symptoms by:‚Å†
‚Å†
üî• creating internal inflammation and immune response‚Å†
üß† damaging the brain and neurotransmitters‚Å†
üö´interfering with proper hormone balance‚Å†
‚Å†
Our bodies have a system designed to process toxins. Your liver and kidneys are powerhouse filters. You eliminate toxins every time you exhale, pee, poop, and sweat.‚Å†
‚Å†
Unfortunately, the body can only process so much junk at one time. It wasn‚Äôt meant to handle the barrage of thousands or even millions of toxins we expose it to every day.‚Å†
‚Å†
Toxins are everywhere and it‚Äôs impossible to avoid them all. Which is why the goal should be to reduce your overall toxic load to a level your body can keep up with.‚Å†
‚Å†
‚úîÔ∏èEat real, whole, organic foods to avoid additives, dyes, pesticides and flavors.‚Å†
‚úîÔ∏èDitch plastic in any way you can to reduce hormone disrupting toxins. Even if it says ‚Äúno BPA‚Äù, it still contains other compounds that wreak havoc on your health.‚Å†
‚úîÔ∏èLimit alcohol to 3-4 drinks per week to free your liver up to filter other toxins.‚Å†
‚úîÔ∏èDrink filtered water to avoid chemicals and heavy metals. We like @berkey_filters. Consider filtering your home‚Äôs water tank.‚Å†
‚úîÔ∏èPurify your indoor air of mold and allergens with a high quality filter like @airdoctorpro.‚Å†
‚úîÔ∏èSwitch to non toxic personal care products and home cleaning products. The @environmentalworkinggroup has a database and many guides to inform your decisions.‚Å†
‚úîÔ∏èReplace your metal tooth fillings ideally under the guidance of a functional dentist familiar with proper removal and body preparation techniques. If it‚Äôs not done right, those heavy metals store in the body and brain.‚Å†
